The paper proposes a novel VAE-based deep auto-encoder model for learning disentangled latent representations in an unsupervised manner. This involves addressing the issue of distinguishing between meaningful and nuisance factors of latent variation. The paper also introduces a suite of disentanglement metrics and demonstrates the model's performance across several benchmark datasets. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
